\subsection{Finrank corollary of the corner-bridge (iter-036)}

The iter-035 corner-bridge $\AffineCoverMVSquare.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}$ is a $k$-linear equivalence; an immediate consequence is that $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,F\,n)$ equals $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X_4)$ for any 2-affine cover. This is the natural follow-on for the genus computation: iter-011 fixed $\genus\,C := \mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$, so the corollary lands $\genus\,C$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ of a chosen 2-affine cover, ready to be evaluated via the iter-029 $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence}$ LES + an iter-037+ affine-vanishing input.

\begin{theorem}[$\HModule$-finrank via $X_4$ corner, abstract sheaf form, iter-036]
  \label{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.finrank_HModule_eq_HModule'_X₄}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv, def:Scheme_HModule, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  Let $k$ be a field, $X : \Scheme$, $S : X.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $F : \Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, $n \in \mathbb{N}$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for the same sheaf category. Then
  \[
    \mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,F\,n)
    \;=\;
    \mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)).
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Apply Mathlib's $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$ ($\mathtt{Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Dimension/Finrank.lean}$) to the symmetric form of the iter-035 corner-bridge $\AffineCoverMVSquare.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}). Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-036 pass) confirms the one-liner $(S.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}\,k\,F\,n).\mathtt{symm}.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$ typechecks end-to-end with kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{theorem}[$\HModule$-finrank via $X_4$ corner, curve form, iter-036]
  \label{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.finrank_HModule_eq_HModule'_X₄_curve}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4, def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $S : C.\mathtt{left}.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $n \in \mathbb{N}$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for $\Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$. Then
  \[
    \mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n)
    \;=\;
    \mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,(\Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)).
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Direct application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} to $F := \Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C$, via the dot-notation method-call form $S.\mathtt{finrank\_HModule\_eq\_HModule}'\_X_4\,k\,\_\,n$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-036 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 closed Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$; iter-035 closed Step 3.5 (the \emph{corner-bridge}) by specialising the iter-034 universal bridge to the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ — both an abstract sheaf form (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}) and a curve specialisation (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}); iter-036 (this iteration) appends the immediate \emph{finrank corollary} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — landing the genus carrier $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ via $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$. The remaining work — Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state) and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-037+.
